Vietnam is a prime example (don't get into whether or not we should have been there, or whether or not we commited enough effort)... enemies knew the land, they dug tunnels and hid.  We need to dump in the "gas," light it and smoke them out is all (yes, I know, over simplification more analogy than realism).<br>
